&lt;p&gt;Our offices are in Emeryville and Santa Clara, California.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About The Role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly technical Engineering Program Manager to lead the development and scaling of Nodes on the Matter Compiler — our modular manufacturing system. You will combine strong technical judgment with program leadership: defining scope and interfaces, setting ownership and success metrics, maintaining integrated plans, and running the operating cadence that drives execution. You will drive programs for integrated machine systems spanning precision motion, optics/metrology, vacuum process modules, embedded software, and factory workcell infrastructure. At Atomic Machines, the PMO is a leverage function. You will strengthen our execution system by tightening feedback loops, reducing friction, clarifying “done,” and surfacing high-integrity signals on progress, risks, and decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end program execution for assigned Nodes, Modules, or Platform initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define scope, milestones, owners, success metrics, and delivery outcomes (time, cost, budget, change control).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional planning across ME, EE, Software, AI, Operations, and Leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain integrated execution plans that connect strategy to daily work, dependencies, and measurable progress.&lt;br&gt;Drive effective change control by framing technical tradeoffs as structured decisions with clear options, risks, and implications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish forecasts, measure execution against them, and improve the mechanisms that increase learning rate and reduce friction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and refine deployment processes for our Hybrid Fab environment to enable rapid design-test-learn cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain dashboards, reviews, and reporting that provide real-time, data-driven visibility into program health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable processes to eliminate recurring challenges (integration, pilot-to-production scaling, cross-team synchronization).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Need:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 (minimum for Senior) to 10+ years spanning hands-on engineering and technical leadership (TPM, engineering management, or equivalent) on complex multidisciplinary products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record delivering integrated hardware-electronics-software systems from concept through manufacturing release.&lt;br&gt;Strong technical fluency grounded in real build experience — able to recognize when a decision requires more rigor vs when to move fast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First-principles thinking with sound instincts for strategic tradeoffs (e.g., buy vs. build, specialization vs. generalization).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with mechanical systems involving motion, kinemat

