&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform visual and dimensional inspections of incoming materials in a timely manner. This includes raw materials and components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhancing and maintaining IQC practices/procedures to support company goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and follow inspection work instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use precision measuring tools such as automated laser measurement systems, CMMs, calipers, micrometers, gauges, and vision systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, enhance, and advise on Standard Operating Procedures and Work Instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a plan and implement a process to clear up a backlog of uninspected materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify materials and parts are in line with drawing requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document inspection results accurately and maintain quality records in accordance with company procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally to develop and implement a deviation process for incoming materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and report non-conformances, aid in driving root cause analysis and corrective/preventive actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with internal quality procedures and applicable industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with production, engineering, and quality teams to support continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in audits, process verifications, and quality review meetings as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean and organized inspection area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
