&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Manufacturing Assembler contractor, you will be responsible for assembling, testing, and packing a variety of mechanical assemblies using hand tools and bench top equipment. The contract length will vary from 3-6 months.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow assembly procedures and work instructions with attention to details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify the integrity of materials to be assembled according to the assembly procedure and/or work instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble components in specific orders, using the proper tooling and equipment specified in the procedures / work instruction instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visual inspection of components and/or assembly according to procedure / work instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and report defective components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the accuracy of work-in-process associated with the work cell.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanliness in your work area and surrounding workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fulfill any other responsibilities as directed and necessary for the business.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need:&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of ISO9001.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use various hand tools such as tweezers, rulers, and cutters tools like torque drivers, torque wrenches, and screwdrivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively as a team member.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to prioritize and organize workload to handle a variety of tasks simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in reading procedures, interpreting visual aids, and following mechanical and electrical drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Precision mechanical component placement and assembly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or equivalent education.&lt;/li&gt;
