&lt;h3&gt;About This Role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Staff Mechanical Systems Engineer at Atomic Machines, you will lead the architecture, design, integration, and validation of precision mechanical systems that enable next-generation manufacturing platforms. You will work across robotics, motion systems, structures, thermal systems, and precision mechanisms to ensure hardware performs reliably as part of tightly integrated electromechanical products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role combines systems engineering leadership with hands-on engineering execution. You will define system architecture while also executing mechanical design, prototype development, integration, and testing activities to validate system performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role may be based out of either office location, Emeryville or Santa Clara, California.&lt;/p&gt;
